review:
I am a stage 3 to 4 cancer survivor .and due to side effects of medications , my 6 set crowns on my front teeth kept getting infected and breaking ( I had an accident when I was very young) .
I am settled in UK . And was running pillar to post in UK and was given 4 months for my entire process to be done. I decided to investigate in Delhi where my parents live.
Dr Sanjay was a rarefind. I connected with him on video call . Following which Dr Sanjay proactively communicated with my doctors and dentists in UK via zoom calls and constantly gave me feedback and treatment route.
I was very impressed by his knowledge,  communication and ability to advise my doctors in UK too.
I finally arrived in Delhi and Dr Sanjay helped me with Blood tests, Scans, explained in detail the full process and always had the time for a quick chat about the surgical process. He was absolutely Brilliant. I have now completed my surgery and aftercare process which too only 10 days . I will be back to Delhi in a couple of months and am looking forward to good dental health and brand new teeth.
reply_text:
Thank you Ayesha for the appreciation and trust.
Looking forward to see you.
My best wishes üôè

tags: None
review:
I found Dr Kumar online after much research. I needed my dental crown replaced, and quickly since I'm only in the country for a short while. I was extremely satisfied with his service.

He was extremely thorough with my checkup, noting shortcomings in my initial root canal (from a different doctor) and making sure the root canal itself was fine. 
He recommended a very wide variety of options of crown replacements, and talked me through my options in language I could understand. 
He was very prompt in getting the crown replaced - new filling, fitting of the crown and the cleaning took only two sittings.
Throughout, he would explain each step of the process making sure I understood what was happening, and answered every random question I would come up with in the sessions with patience and precision.
He was very responsive to my body language and doubts, and went out of the way to make sure I was satisfied with his work.
Finally, he was very reasonable and up-front about the costs involved, and I had a clear idea of what each step would cost me from the get-go. 

My only hesitation was when I saw how unassuming his lab appeared, but don't let that fool you in the slightest. They've got (what my untrained eye finds to be) good equipment, and I now have a new crown, and a bar-coded card with a 10 year replacement warranty to keep me at ease.

10/10 will be getting checkups from him whenever I'm in town.

review: Dr. Kumar was recommended to me by my family members, who are his regular clients. I also read many positive reviews online so I decided to schedule an appointment to fix the enamel erosion on my upper molar tooth. I visited Dr. Kumar's dental clinic in Greater Kailash-1 and was impressed by the state-of-the-art facilities and the cleanliness. After a quick examination, Dr. Kumar explained the problem to me and fixed the enamel erosion within no time. He has a friendly, solution-centric approach which makes patients feel comfortable. He also went out of his way to answer all my questions and clear any doubts that I had. The thing that impressed me most about Dr. Kumar is that he doesn't increase the number of sittings just to make extra money - something which most dentists do nowadays. Customer satisfaction is the only thing that matters to him. I would definitely recommend Dr. Kumar to anyone looking for a good dentist.
